# Migration Rules

Purpose:
Control changes to SQLite schema, initialization, and data evolution.

Rules:
- Keep schema changes explicit.
- Prefer simple, reviewable migration steps over generic migration frameworks unless the project explicitly introduces one.
- Do not use ORM-based migration tools.
- Keep schema initialization idempotent.
- If the schema changes, update the initialization path and relevant tests in the same change.
- Preserve backward readability of existing persisted data when reasonably possible.
- Do not mix schema changes with unrelated refactors.
- Document any new tables, columns, or constraints in architecture or operational docs when relevant.
- Keep raw SQL readable and formatted.
- If startup behavior depends on schema initialization, make it deterministic and safe to rerun.

Expected behavior:
- Database evolution remains simple and auditable.
- Schema changes are easy to reason about.
- Runtime initialization stays predictable.